           <h2>Almonds</h2>
           <div class="xyz">
               <div class="pqr">
                Almonds are jam-packed with many of the vitamins and minerals necessary for growing taller.

Besides bringing a host of healthy fats to the table, they’re high in fiber, manganese, and magnesium .

Plus, almonds are rich in vitamin E, a fat-soluble vitamin that doubles as an antioxidant.

A deficiency in this important vitamin can come with serious side effects, including stunted growth in children .

Almonds may also help foster bone health. In one small study in 14 people, consuming almonds was found to inhibit the formation of osteoclasts, which are a type of cell that breaks down bone tissue.
               
               
