           <h2>Eggs</h2>
           <div class="xyz">
               <div class="pqr">
                Eggs are truly a powerhouse of nutrition.

They’re especially rich in protein, with 6 grams packed into a single large egg .

Plus, they contain a wealth of other vitamins and minerals necessary for growth, including vitamin D, which can increase calcium absorption to help maintain skeletal health.

One small study found that giving children with low vitamin D levels a vitamin D supplement resulted in increased growth over a 6-month period.

What’s more, one study in 874 children observed that regularly eating eggs was associated with increased monthly height gains .
           
                
           
